HEADWORD: Sandhiller
<hw>Sand"hill`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A nickname given
to any ⟦ldquo⟧poor white⟦rdquo⟧ living in the pine woods which cover the
sandy hills in Georgia and South Carolina.</def> <mark>[U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sandiness</ent>⟦br⟧
